Alien Invasion

by: Sameer Prakash

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I enjoy medium-paced 'relaxing' games where you can play on for a long time. I was thinking of doing something completely different, but I ended up using League Invaders as a base to create Alien Invasion with two extra game phases, more objects, and a 'riddle' at the end. Soon enough, I created a game that I really liked!

2. What I Learned

After testing, I found out that some parts of the game were too easy, so I made it harder by decreasing the projectile cooldown and adding a time limit. I also added a new, more powerful type of alien after testing and made the car able to shoot in multiple directions.

3. Architecture of My Game

Alien Invasion has different classes for every object in the game (the rocket, car, aliens, asteroids, etc.), an Object Manager that draws and updates the objects, and a Game Panel where all the objects are shown. All the game objects are accessed in the object managers, which are accessed in the game panel, which is accessed in the main JFrame.

4. Technical Implementation

I'm proud of some of the OS-level things and extra features I added to the game, like a command line (type 'easter egg'), a preferences menu, and a way to switch between all the modes using keyboard shortcuts. On macOS, I also made the menu bar appear in the system menu bar at the top of the screen. I also added a file that reads and writes all your scores so they are saved even when you close the window.

5. Most Challenging Part

One challenge that I faced was that classes were not behaving the way I wanted them to. Sometimes, the images wouldn't load or the objects would move in the wrong direction, but usually, it was pretty easy to find my mistakes or move around my code.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

I tried to make the application more like a native Mac app by adding a preferences menu to the app-menu bar, but after trying out one of Apple's solutions from the pre-Mavericks area, it ended up not working. I might search for a way to do this in the future. I also might add some more game phases in the future, but currently, I'm really proud of my game!
